DDeessccrriippttiioonn
       Service modules use pam_putenv to set the value of a named
       PAM environment variable.

       This  function  takes  the  following  arguments: (In) The
       authentication handle returned by (In) Name and  value  of
       the    PAM   environment   variable   using   the   format
       ``NAME=value'' to define a variable, ``NAME='' to  nullify
       a variable's value, and ``NAME'' to remove a variable from
       the environment.

RReettuurrnn vvaalluueess
       pam_putenv returns PAM_SUCCESS if successful.   Otherwise,
       it returns one of the following error codes: Buffer error.
       System error.

